&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optical Services clerical officer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Area of WorkSt. James’s UniversityHospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EmployerLeeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DepartmentOptometry&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LocationLeeds&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary£18,005 - £19,337 pro rata per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per Week37.5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job TypePermanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pay Scheme Band2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date13/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited to join the administration team in the Optometry department based in the Eye clinic, Ground floor, Chancellors Wing, St. James’s UniversityHospital. This is a permanent post. You will help in providing administrative support for the Optometrists and dispensing opticians including booking appointments on the Trust PAS system, organising Optometric and dispensing optician files and setting up clinics, filing optometry record cards, dealing with patient’s telephone and email queries, posting out optical appliances to patients and taking payments for spectacles and contact lenses from patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In joining our team you will help us to provide the highest quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Hours: 37.5 per week (applicants wishing to job share are welcomed)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: Band 2 - £18,005 - £19,337 pro rata per annum (depending on skills &amp; experience)&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; For further information contact Dianne Wilford, Optical Services Officer on 64452 or Tim Hunter, Head of Optometry Services by email tim.hunter1@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Please note if you are successful in obtaining an interview you will be notified via email. You will be given a minimum of 1 weeks notice, prior to your interview date. If you have not heard from us within 3 weeks of the closing date, please assume that your application has not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
